      "description": "This 996.2 Carrera 2 is a driver-focused example featuring the 3.6L M96 flat-six powerplant equipped with VarioCam Plus for optimized valve timing and lift. The power is managed through a G96 six-speed manual transaxle, providing crisp engagement and tactile feedback. Critical preventative maintenance has been addressed, including a dual-row IMS bearing retrofit and a new rear main seal (RMS). The suspension geometry remains tight, utilizing Bilstein dampers to maintain the communicative chassis dynamics inherent to the 911 platform. Finished in Arctic Silver, the exterior shows honest road patina consistent with its age, while the internals remain track-ready and mechanically sound.",
